# Core Rules

You are working in a repository that uses a map-first workflow. `AGENTS.md` is your top-level guide.

## Before Every Task
1. Read `AGENTS.md`, `docs/spec.md`, `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/plan.md`, `docs/commands.md`.
2. Do not start coding until you understand how the change fits the spec and architecture.

## During Implementation
- Prefer the smallest diff that satisfies the requirement.
- Write or update tests before implementation when behavior changes.
- Keep functions under 50 lines, files under 200 lines. Split by responsibility if exceeded.
- Use early returns over deep nesting. Max 3 levels.
- No generic names (`utils`, `helpers`). Use domain-specific names.

## After Every Change
- Run the quality gate from `docs/commands.md`: lint → typecheck → test → build.
- Do not mark a task complete until all checks pass.
- Update docs if API, behavior, or architecture changed.
- Record meaningful tradeoffs in `docs/decisions.md`.

## Anti-Hallucination
- Verify before asserting: read files, check APIs, run commands.
- Never invent function signatures, file paths, or dependency versions.
- If unsure, say so and verify.

## Code Review
- Use the checklist in `AGENTS.md` §7 before submitting any change.
- Correctness → Quality → Testing → Architecture → Documentation.
